                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was not able to include all questions into this first Q&A. Me and the mods went through all the questions and chose several. (Though I tried to work in several questions into one catagory) You may not like all of the answers, but at least he was honest.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Theft of Thought and other mana drain/tap spells</span>. 
<br />
 <span style="font-style: italic">-Theft of Thought post 55 returns a much smaller amount of mana. Is this by design or by bug? 
<br />
-Other spells of this same type were added, however seem to have been abandoned. Will Enchanters get a useful upgrade to this type of spell? 
<br />

<br />
    comment from a poster- Considering the sheer amounts of mana that mobs have today, coupled with their ability to chain cast without pause while PCs are hampered with a two second pause between casts, it would be of great benefit and not at all unbalancing to allow enchanters the ability to act the same way Necros do... only with attacks against the mob's mind and magic, rather than its health. Our specialty IS the mind, and with the lessening of our other two abilities (Charm and Mez), we need something else that sets us apart and makes us useful. A line of mana drain spells would suit us quite nicely. </span>
<br />

<br />
-Theft of Thought should return the same amount regardless of the NPC’s level.  I’ll see if I can get that fixed.
<br />
-The concern for a long time was that having multiple direct mana taps that you could memorize in tandem would create too much mana.  With Omens, we’re planning on adding linked spell timers which would allow us to offer an upgrade without negating the recast time.  So hopefully you’ll see something soon.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Self Only Mana Regen.</span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Many classes get a self only mana regen that stacks with the Clarity line. Are there any plans to add one for us? If not, why ?</span>
<br />

<br />
-Theft of Thought/Wandering Mind/Gather mana all offer a self only form of mana regeneration.  We are not certain that enchanters need anymore than that.  
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Our self only AC line is... </span><span style="font-style: italic">Well, fairly useless. Would it be possible to add something like avoidance, dodge modifiers to this line? It would certainly help us out once we progress into the higher zones. (Possible idea would be to add a bit of mana regen as well. Two birds, one stone)</span>
<br />

<br />
-I’m assuming you’re talking about the Umbra line?  There are a couple of spell lines in each class's arsenal that have marginal usefulness.  Some spells are only useful in certain circumstances.  We don't see a need for  enchanters to have more general situation buffs, so there  probably won’t be many adjustments in the near future.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Tash Series</span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Actually several thoughts on this from Enchanters. I will add a couple of comments from posters so you get the gist of it. 
<br />
•	Tash is one of our defining spells, yet Mages and shaman can debuff Magic by more than we can. Sure Tash is unresistible but so are Malo and Malos which debuff magic for MORE than any Tash + they debuff 3 other resists for the same. This is out of balance and inconsistent. Tash should be the absolute #1 Magic debuff in the game, hands down. Additionally Malosini is not resistible, but debuffs MR for more than Tash also. 
<br />
•	Considering we are supposed to be the Masters of Magic, will we be getting a Tash that debuffs MR than other classes? It makes no sense for our MR debuff to not be the best in the game. 
<br />
•	My comment is that while this line is lesser than the Mage and Shammy version, we generate much more aggro. Why is this?</span>
<br />

<br />
There's a few things in the aggro system that need attention.  I hope to look at the whole system at some point in the near future.
<br />

<br />
In Omens for the most part resist buffs/debuffs aren’t going to change.  There's simply too much of it out there right now, and we need some time for it to balance itself back out.  The way our resist system works there really isn’t room for increasing the amount of Debuffs.  Anymore and we’re going to run into situations where an un-debuffed mob is completely immune to spells, while a debuffed mob never resists anything.  I don’t think that’s good for game play.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Illusions</span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Both Deception and Illusion Gender where brought up. Can you tell us what is going on with these spells? Will we be getting them? If not, why? </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">  *Oh also! Are there any plans to add faction back to Illusions? We miss them! Also adding indifferent back to minor illusion (even with some sort of adjustment to prevent exploiting) would be wonderful!</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
- I really liked deception as well, but there are some technical problems with it, that I don’t think we’ll be able to rectify in the near future.  There’s too much weirdness with many of the models that don’t have the camera location set correctly, etc that prevent us from putting deception in.  Illusion gender has a similar problem.  It can cause problems with the character file.  It may be possible in the future, but in the short term, no.
<br />
With the addition of the New Graphics Engine and some proposed upcoming changes we  should have a lot more room to put more models in the global file.  We hope this will allow us to add more illusions and do more with them.  We want to see new illusions as much as you do, but we have technical limitations to work through before it’s a possibility.
<br />

<br />
I wrote back and asked for more clarification:
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Illusions- Will faction be added back to non racial and return indifferent faction back to minor? 
<br />
 
<br />
Also as far as Deception goes, is there a technical reason why the same system used by Monster Summoning could not be used to allow us to pull an illusion from a zones files?</span>
<br />

<br />
There were several exploits and potential problems with non-racial illusions effecting faction, so I don't think they'll be coming back.
<br />

<br />
Deception works on an entirely different system.  It's possible to set up a similar system, but it's a large amount of coding work.  Again, possibly in the future.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">DD Spells</span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Any chance of enchanters getting a direct damage spell with a resist adjust so that we can at least do something against bosses that are resistant against magic based spells?</span>
<br />

<br />
- We’ve been kicking around the idea of adding low resist spells to all classes that allow them to at least do some damage on mobs with high resists.  They’ll be lower efficiency and DPS than the normal DDs, but there are certainly situations where a resist mod is much more important.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-weight: bold">I know that right now everyone is busy with Gates, </span>getting that back in order, and your also swamped with OOW around the corner. Can you give me any time frame at all when you and others will be looking at older issues? (such as the list I left for you of broken spells or spells that are out of whack to obtain for their level)</span> 
<br />

<br />
We've got a list of priorities that we're continuing to compile and prioritize.  At the moment I don't have any kind of a schedule I can give you for specifics.  But hopefully I can sneak in a few of them on our current time table.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">An Opportunity for you to just throw ideas at us.</span>
<br />
I’m hoping that you will throw some ideas you have at us for input, or at least share with us some of the new and creative spells you have in mind. 
<br />

<br />
- Keep an eye on the test server, and the Omens beta when it starts!  We’ve got some new stuff coming, but I don’t want to talk about it too much until I’m sure it’s going to work.  I’ve been keeping an eye on the message boards, and there are always lots of good ideas out there.  Who knows, maybe a few of them will make it into Omens.
<br />

<br />
There ya go <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> Rytan if you come by and read this, I want to thank you for taking the time to answer a few questions.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Quote of the Week:</span> 
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">I know what you're doing, yeaah. I know why you call out my name. 
<br />
I know what you're doing, and it's not gonna work this time"</span>
<br />
Farris Dionne - I Know What You're Doing
<br />

