</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Theft of Thought/Wandering Mind/Gather mana all offer a self only form of mana regeneration. We are not certain that enchanters need anymore than that. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is a pretty clueless response. Mana Taps are not the same as mana regen buffs. They require that they remain memmed, and that you have a caster handy to use them on. GM is a panic ability. People who divide mana regained from GM over refresh time and call that 'mana/tick' don't understand how it is most often used. NOBODY nukes/mezzes/buffs down to zero mana then hits GM just as it refreshes.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">-I’m assuming you’re talking about the Umbra line? There are a couple of spell lines in each class's arsenal that have marginal usefulness. Some spells are only useful in certain circumstances. We don't see a need for enchanters to have more general situation buffs, so there probably won’t be many adjustments in the near future. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Wordplay. Umbra line is not marginal, it is <span style="font-weight: bold">useless</span>. There is no reason to mem it or waste a slot on it (may the church of Umbra forgive me).
