                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Quote: 
<br />
Theft of Thought/Wandering Mind/Gather mana all offer a self only form of mana regeneration. We are not certain that enchanters need anymore than that.  
<br />

<br />
And somehow, the Forceshield line that Wizards and Necros have keep giving more mana with no consequences.
<br />

<br />
And somehow, Necros keep getting higher mana regen each expansion, AND the greater Forceshield line, AND have the group wide mana tap.
<br />

<br />
And somehow, clerics keep getting better zealot lines and yaulp lines.  Even hybrids are getting better personal mana regen rates.
<br />

<br />
In theory you could mem all these spells and chain them, BUT who ever would.  Who has the spell slot space.  Even if we could, how would this make or break the game, since we can't share that mana.  Oh my gosh we could actually have a choice of whether we wanted to nuke more rather than charm because we were flat out tired that night and didn't want to be quite as attentive (or charm wasn't available, which puts us as the crappiest DPS class in the game).  That would make us less efficient, but give US the choice.  It would do little to nothing in the very highend game because of the buffs that raiders already run around with, BUT it would help in the low and mid game where the most help is needed.
<br />

<br />
Here's where the lack of thought irritates me.  They did the same thing with my mage with pet canni, comparing acitive and passive regen.  It was proved that in reality you could achieve (if you were really working hard clicking buttons) FT35 since while you canni you can't do anything else.  It was great for downtime after deaths where you could achieve much higher levels of FT or when the cleric went afk for a couple of min.  Other than that it was a useful tool that put us at necromancer mana regen levels.  And still they nerfed it.  Same here, there shortsightedness has turned theory into reality in there minds with no justification or logical conclusions drawn.
<br />

<br />
So here's my suggestion, turn arcane rune into the forceshield line.  Add a FT component to it.  Put a 5 mana per tick component to it and call it a day.  Up it to 7 with the new OoW spell.
<br />

<br />
And as far as the Umbra line goes I think it is silly.  All other AC lines are described as "hardening" your defenses (i.e. making your skin harder).  Ours puts an illusion around the target.  Therefore, both should stack.  Here's theory and reality again kids, "What tank would take up a valuable buff slot for another 35 AC when they are already at 1600+AC?"  Answer no one.  However, this extra buff would be great for the caster trying to get over the 900AC soft cap.  I know my mage is EP flagged with a few pieces of EP gear (retired him) and he never made it over that cap.  Not as important for him, but my enchanter is constantly being beat on and would be great for him.
<br />

<br />
So in conclusion, theory and reality rarely collide.  Realize that and move on.  When posed with a problem, examine the "real" consequences rather than the fairy tale consequences.
<br />

<br />
That is all..............</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
