                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1.  We say, "Tash is underpowered in comparison with everyone else's debuffs."
<br />

<br />
Rytan says, "Debuffs are too powerful, so we are not changing them."
<br />

<br />
If you are convinced by this argument, Arthur Anderson would like to nominate you to the Board of Directors of the SEC.
<br />

<br />
2.  Looks like we are getting a lure nuke, and therefore going from "After the buff-cycle, I type '/follow' and go watch TV" to "Hey, I am level 50 wizard!"  Super.  While this is sorta-good for some folks, it's terrible that this is the only thing worthwhile in the post.
<br />

<br />
3.  Umbra
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Rytan wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">There are a couple of spell lines in each class's arsenal that have marginal usefulness. Some spells are only useful in certain circumstances.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
A couple of spell lines?!!!  This ranks right up there with the "Oh -- there is still a 'spell recovery time not met' bug?"  Do they have anyone there who plays an enchanter?  Do they have anyone who might be willing to log into the test server and type "/testbuff".  A couple of spell lines?!!!  I'm estimating half of the spells in my spellbook I only cast one or two times -- just to see what they did.  That's 50% -- and that's a bit more than "a couple of spell lines".
<br />

<br />
4.  The Final Straw
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Rytan wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Keep an eye on the test server, and the Omens beta when it starts!  We’ve got some new stuff coming, but I don’t want to talk about it too much until I’m sure it’s going to work.  I’ve been keeping an eye on the message boards, and there are always lots of good ideas out there.  Who knows, maybe a few of them will make it into Omens.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Isn't this the same sort of "We know best" attitude that they said they were going to change at the summit?  Or was that just pillow-talk?
<br />

<br />
Just as a hint, "We know best" only works when you demonstrate competence and are conversant with the issues, neither of which you demonstrated here.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
